On October 7, 2023, senior soldier of the National Guard of Ukraine Artem Igorevich Zazyan died in a military medical institution in Kyiv.

Artyom was assigned to military service, after which he served under a contract in 2021. He served as an intelligence officer for one of the special forces units of the National Guard of Ukraine.

On October 2, Artyom was seriously wounded in battles near the village of Stelmakha, Svatovsky district, Lugansk region.

Farewell to Artem Igorevich Zazyan will take place on October 10 at 13:00 in the village of Ukrainka of the Krinichansky territorial society. The warrior will be buried in the same village in the rural cemetery.

We express our sincere condolences to the mother, stepfather, brother, sister and uncle of the deceased warrior who fought for our country.
where_description: near the village of Stelmakha, Svatovsky district, Lugansk region
